offer_summary.company_name: HSBC Service Delivery (Polska) Sp. z o.o.
offer_summary.location: hybrid work - Warsaw, ност відкритий для українців
offer_summary.job_description: As Python Developer, you will contribute to the construction and testing of analytic platforms. You will play a key role in accelerating development of prototypes that could materially influence risk analysis and measurement at HSBC.
requirements: MSc or PhD in a technical field such as Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, Operational Research and/or Information Systems (Informatics) or similar.
3 years of experience building and testing applications in a professional environment.
requiered_skills: Solid experience developing applications using an object oriented programming language (e.g. Java, C++, C# or Python).
Some knowledge of the more common design patterns.
Experience working with non-traditional database architectures (such as column free / NoSQL / graph-theoretic structures).
nice_to_have_skills: Some experience programming in a mathematical or engineering technical environment (such as MATLAB).
Familiarity with algorithms for capturing and processing large datasets (i.e. Map/Reduce).
Experience developing in an Agile environment with continuous integration practices.
benefits: One-time reimbursement of home office set-up (up to 800 PLN). Corporate parties & events
Financial support with trainings and education
Sharing the costs of sports activities
Sharing the costs of professional training & courses
Doctor's duty hours in the office
Opportunity to obtain permits and licenses
